=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bqt1665702871452.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqt1665702871452.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bqt1665702871452.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bqt1665702871452\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Open Widget Interface\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Physical widgets for Form components are implemented using the Open Widget Interface (OWI). The OWI is an API that defines how widgets are included in Uniface components and how they interact with data.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqt1665702871452__p_d25529e1_d25530e1_d25531e1\">It is possible to incorporate other widgets into Uniface using the OWI. For example, the Uniface calendar widget is really an OWI-implemented wrapper around the Microsoft Windows calendar control.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bqt1665702871452__p_d25532e1_d25533e1_d25534e1\">The OWI is available as a set of header files (<span class=\"ph filepath\">o*.h</span>) in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">3GL/include</span> directory of the Uniface installation.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Although Unifields and labels are functionally equivalent to logical widgets, they are not true widgets, and are not addressed using the OWI.</div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The names of all physical widgets supplied with Uniface begin with the letter U, so avoid giving your custom widgets physical names beginning with U.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526191\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526191\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Open Widget Interface Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Open Widget Interface Physical widgets for Form components are implemented using the Open Widget Interface (OWI). The OWI is an API that defines how widgets are included in Uniface components and how they interact with data. It is possible to incorporate other widgets into Uniface using the OWI. For example, the Uniface calendar widget is really an OWI-implemented wrapper around the Microsoft Windows calendar control. The OWI is available as a set of header files ( o*.h ) in the 3GL/include directory of the Uniface installation. Note: Although Unifields and labels are functionally equivalent to logical widgets, they are not true widgets, and are not addressed using the OWI. Note: The names of all physical widgets supplied with Uniface begin with the letter U, so avoid giving your custom widgets physical names beginning with U. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}